track_notes: I am uploading this track in March 2018. I do not think the SMP was in being then, hence it was forgotten.  I cannot recall much about the walk as it was 12 years ago. My XYL and I completed it and I cannot recall any specific problems.

Here is the route I took. 

I parked in a quarry on the side of the forest road.

The first leg follows the pylons. There a tracks in the cutting. After leaving the pylons, an easier route up would be to use the route  I used to descend. There is a drainage ditch on the side of the forest and the gradient is not so steep, but you do loose time on the ridge.

The 2nd leg from GM/SS-178 to GM/SS-092 I would have been better to route to the north of Munwhul to hit the forest road without entering the forest. 

The 3rd leg is back to the forest road and descend back to the parking.

Most of the route is tussocks so is not quick. Follow the deer tracks to make it a bit easier.

The walk time was about 4 hours.
